<div class="heading-box">
<h1 class="main-title">WebCodeGenie</h1>
<h2 class="sub-title">Terms and Conditions</h2>
</div>
<div class="blog-content">
<div class="content-box">
<h3>General Work Terms and Client Responsibilities & Liabilities</h3>
<ul>
<li>All site content (text and multimedia) will be the sole responsibility of the client to provide to
 Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD. Such should be provided prior to commencing the work.</li>
<li>Client is solely responsible to take proper back-up of all content on their site prior to letting
 Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD undertake the required course of action towards meeting the contract. Any
loss or damage to existing data shall not be a responsibility of Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD under any
circumstances.</li>
<li>The Contract does not hold Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD responsible for any data entry, web hosting or
custom artwork/graphics related work/tasks unless otherwise specifically mentioned, paid for and agreed to
by both the parties towards such. Any artwork, images, or text supplied and/or designed by Shivay infotech
Technology PVT LTD on behalf of the client, will remain the property of Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD
and/or it's suppliers unless otherwise agreed.</li>
<li>While Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD will do its best to achieve all deliveries within the estimated time,
there may, at times, be the need to extend or adjust time in cases of any unavoidable and non-forecasted
situations like those of deployment issues, dependencies, 3rd-Party support, development bottle-necks,
resource unavailability due to emergency, communication delays and the like.</li>
<li> Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD will provide the Client an opportunity to review the appearance and content
of the Web site during the design and once they are completed. Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD shall wait
for a period of 7 days to hear any feedback on such shared work/outputs from the client. In the event of
client not replying within this period, such material will deemed to have been automatically accepted and
approved by the Client.</li>
<li>The Client retains the copyright to data, files and graphic logos provided by the Client and grants
 Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD the rights to publish and use such material. The Client must obtain
permission and rights to use any information or files that are copyrighted by a third party. The Client is
further responsible for granting Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD permission and rights for use of the same
and agrees to indemnify and hold harmless Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD from any and all claims resulting
from the Client's negligence or inability to obtain proper copyright permissions. A contract for Web
site design and/or placement shall be regarded as a guarantee by the Client to Shivay infotechTechnology PVT
LTD that all such permissions and authorities have been obtained. Evidence of permissions and authorities
may be requested.</li>
<li> Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD will not accept responsibility for any alterations caused by the Client or a
third party occurring to the Client's pages/website once installed/deployed. Such alterations include,
but are not limited to additions, modifications or deletions. Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD may require a
one-off Web Development charge before resolving any issues that may arise.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="content-box">
<h3>Payments</h3>
<ul>
<li> Shivay infotechTechnology PVT LTD accepts payments by cheque, Cash or Bank Transfers (although we reserve the
right to decline payment in any of these forms without notice). Without limitation, Shivay infotechTechnology
PVT LTD reserves the right to withdraw any payment methods at any time and to vary its prices without prior
notice.</li>
<li>A cancellation fee may be charged if the Customer cancels the Service prior to completion. The fee will be
equal to the amount of work completed at the point of cancellation.</li>
<li>A non-payment of cancellation fee and/or over-due amount will result in legal action upon necessity.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="content-box">
<h3>Support and 3rd-Party</h3>
<ul>
<li>As the site launches, we offer free support for the first month. After one month of free service, we charge
according to our various price packages best-suited to client&#039;s requirement. We also provide attractive
discounts if the client chooses a higher price package. The scope of support only includes any bug fixing
and email support and excludes any issues related to the site architecture, rule changes and
add-ons/enhancements.</li>
<li>Any 3rd-Party support, product and/or service being used/ integrated into the site which requires licensing,
